<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="1528" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1528">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.41/393.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Letcher</persName> to
                                    the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 627.]</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Chihuahua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-27">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 27, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the Department’s No. 350
                                of April 6, 1915, relative to the depredations being committed on
                                the ranch property belonging to the estate of the late W. S. Benton,
                                I have the honor to report that I have suggested to Mr. Harvie,
                                resident manager of the property, that he take the matter up with
                                the British Vice Consul. I have also conferred with the latter and
                                offered him my cooperation in further proceedings on his part, as
                                instructed in the Department’s communication under
                                acknowledgment.</p>
                            <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Marion Letcher.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>